content:
After assigning permission sets with either basic or advanced setup, follow these optional procedures to enhance the CRM Analytics experience and fine-tune CRM Analytics access to Salesforce data.

Enable Previews for All Assets
Make it easier for users to browse analytics assets in collections.
Enable CRM Analytics for Experience Cloud Sites
Securely share CRM Analytics apps with an Experience Cloud site partner and customer users.
Enable Conversational Exploration
Quickly query and visualize data in guided, natural language conversations.
Enable Search Insights (Ask Data for Salesforce)
Bring intelligent, self-service analytics to the CRM Analytics Home page.
Enable Direct Data in CRM Analytics
Run queries directly against external data sources.
Enable the CRM Analytics REST API
Access CRM Analytics datasets and lenses programmatically using the CRM Analytics REST API.
Enable Dashboard Views
Allow each CRM Analytics user to create their own unique views of a dashboard.
Enable Annotations on Dashboard Widgets
Annotate dashboard widgets with comments posted in the dashboard and in Chatter.
Enable Unified Analytics
Unify your reports and dashboards and CRM Analytics items on the Analytics tab in Salesforce and Analytics Studio.
Enable CRM Analytics Watchlist
Capture and track up to 20 KPIs across different dashboards, plus historical trending.
Enable Downloading Data from CRM Analytics
Enable users to download results from lens explorations and dashboard widgets as Microsoft Excel or comma-separated values files.
Secure Image Sharing and Downloading
Control who shares dashboard and lens images to prevent sensitive images from being shared.
Enable Null Measure Handling in Orgs Created Before Spring â€™17
Specify null as the default value for numeric columns in recipes, dataflows, and CSV uploads.
Open Salesforce Records from CRM Analytics dashboards in New Browser Tabs
Change the default behavior of selecting a Salesforce record action to open the record in a new browser tab.
Enable Custom Fiscal Year Support
Inherit custom fiscal years in CRM Analytics.
Enable Data Manager (Legacy)
Update and create dataflows as you migrate them to data prep recipes.
Enable Custom Time Zones
View time-specific data on dashboards in a time zone that you specify for your org.
Disable Input Caching for Recipes
Prevent input caching when running recipes.
Control Which Analytics Tab Users Access the Analytics Studio
Specify who can create apps and edit and delete datasets and dashboards by making Analytics Studio invisible to Analytics Tab users on a per profile basis.
title: Enhancing CRM Analytics Experience
